Pinkerton ' s Inc abandons planned acquisition . Pinkerton ' s Inc said Friday that it had ended discussions with Sensormatic Electronics Corp on the proposed acquisition of Sensormatic ' s Enterprise Accounts Division and central station non - retail monitoring business . Pinkerton said the deal was quashed after an extensive due diligence investigation . The deal was originally announced in May . Terms were not disclosed . " We are moving forward immediately with the acquisition of high - quality integrators in our targeted geographic areas , " Pinkerton Executive Vice President Michael Carter said in a statement . " We continue with our objective to complete the building of Pinkerton ' s U . S . systems integration division through internal growth and acquisitions as soon as possible . " ( ( - - New York Newsdesk 212 - 859 - 1610 ) ) 
